                        <h4 class="title2 -t:5" >
    <span>Why medical staff shortages have been a chronic problem
    </span>
</h4>
            <p class="lead2">When the Department of Health moved out of Hawkins House into its shiny new home on ­Baggot Street, did anyone bother to bring the dusty old pile of reports on medical workforce planning? The Hanly report, the MacCraith report and so on - they made for good reading, but the failure to implement their recommendations has meant that Ireland&#039;s hospitals remain ­woefully understaffed.</p>                    </a>
            </div>
    </article>
